                    <p><i>"That's what he says about every film. Remember 'Nocturnal Emissions'? He called it 'Bergman meets Brazzers' and it was just people fucking in a cemetery."</i></p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="vhs-effect">
                        <img src="/api/placeholder/280/280" alt="Tav">
                    </div>
                    <h3>Tav</h3>
                    <p>Cinematographer. Her copper-red hair pulled back in a practical ponytail, but a few strands escape to frame a face that suggests both artistic vision and the ability to field-strip a camera in under two minutes.</p>
                    <p><i>"The movie's actually going to be brilliant. Because he's a self-obsessed maniac, but he's a genius self-obsessed maniac."</i></p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="vhs-effect">
                        <img src="/api/placeholder/280/280" alt="Karlach">
                    </div>
                    <h3>Karlach</h3>
                    <p>Equipment Manager. Six-foot-something of pure muscle wrapped in a faded Metallica t-shirt with the sleeves ripped off, arms covered in burn scars that tell stories of electrical mishaps and too many all-nighters with faulty equipment.</p>
                    <p><i>"Still better than the director who tried to set me on fire for 'authentic lighting effects.'"</i></p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="featured">
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="vhs-effect">
                        <img src="/api/placeholder/280/280" alt="Gale">
                    </div>
                    <h3>Gale</h3>
                    <p>Assistant Director. His movement a chaotic whirlwind of enthusiasm and academic urgency. Three pencils protrude from his messy bun, and his clipboard is covered in both shooting notes and obscure magical symbols.</p>
                    <p><i>"It's brilliant, really. The mise en abyme of it all—the infinite regression of reality folding in on itself. It's a perfect metaphor for the human condition!"</i></p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="vhs-effect">
                        <img src="/api/placeholder/280/280" alt="Wyll">
                    </div>
                    <h3>Wyll</h3>
                    <p>Financial Manager. Dressed in an immaculate button-down shirt that somehow remains unwrinkled despite the chaos of film production, a calculator visible in his breast pocket, and his single eye focused on something in the middle distance as if reviewing spreadsheets in his mind.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="vhs-effect">
                        <img src="/api/placeholder/280/280" alt="Lae'zel">
