        <section id="about">
            <h2>ABOUT THE STUDIO</h2>
            <div class="vhs-effect">
                <img src="/api/placeholder/600/300" alt="Crimson Ecstasy Studios" style="max-width:100%; margin-bottom:20px;">
            </div>
            <p>Crimson Ecstasy Productions is an independent studio headquartered in a converted Gothic revival church in the Hollywood Hills (purchased at foreclosure after a particularly scandalous incident involving the previous religious occupants). The building is perpetually illuminated by hundreds of red candles, creating both an atmosphere Astarion deems "appropriately sensual" and what the fire marshal describes as "a lawsuit waiting to happen."</p>
            <p>Though Astarion is not, technically speaking, a vampire (a fact he sometimes clarifies with the specific phrasing "not in the traditional sense"), he cultivates an aesthetic that leaves the question deliberately ambiguous. His refusal to be photographed eating, his exclusively nocturnal shooting schedule, his preference for wine served in crystal goblets, and his habit of occasionally running his tongue over his slightly-too-sharp canines while making eye contact with uncomfortable actors all contribute to the industry rumor that he is "definitely something."</p>
            <p>Astarion employs a full-time "Entrance Coordinator" whose sole responsibility is ensuring optimal lighting conditions for his arrivals and exits. This individual—a former theatrical lighting designer who had worked on Broadway before a nervous breakdown led him to Los Angeles—has installed a complex system of remote-controlled lights throughout all Crimson Ecstasy facilities.</p>
            <a href="#full-story" class="btn">Full Studio History</a>
        </section>
        
